
\S operand \S

An operand is an "argument"\S*\S to a command that specifies the
files or directories that the command is to operate on. For example,
in the command

	pr temp

the "file name"\S*\S "temp" is an operand that specifies the input
file for the print command, pr(1).

\S*\S defined in the \Sglossary\S
